[{},{"attrs":{"title":"API: Nuxt(options)","description":"You can use Nuxt.js programmatically to use it as a middleware giving you the freedom of creating your own server for rendering your web applications."},"body":"<h1><a id=\"using-nuxt-js-programmatically\" class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"#using-nuxt-js-programmatically\"><svg version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" class=\"octicon octicon-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"/></svg></a>Using Nuxt.js Programmatically</h1><p>You might want to use your own server with your middleware and your API. That&#39;s why you can use Nuxt.js programmatically.</p>\n<p>You can require Nuxt.js like this:</p>\n<pre><code class=\"hljs js\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\">const</span> { Nuxt, Builder } = <span class=\"hljs-built_in\">require</span>(<span class=\"hljs-string\">'nuxt'</span>)</code></pre><h2><a id=\"nuxt-constructor\" class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"#nuxt-constructor\"><svg version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" class=\"octicon octicon-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"/></svg></a>Nuxt Constructor</h2><p>To see the list of options to give to Nuxt.js, see the configuration section.</p>\n<pre><code class=\"hljs js\"><span class=\"hljs-comment\">// Require `Nuxt` And `Builder` modules</span>\n<span class=\"hljs-keyword\">const</span> { Nuxt, Builder } = <span class=\"hljs-built_in\">require</span>(<span class=\"hljs-string\">'nuxt'</span>)\n\n<span class=\"hljs-comment\">// Require Nuxt config</span>\n<span class=\"hljs-keyword\">const</span> config = <span class=\"hljs-built_in\">require</span>(<span class=\"hljs-string\">'./nuxt.config.js'</span>)\n\n<span class=\"hljs-comment\">// Create a new Nuxt instance</span>\n<span class=\"hljs-keyword\">const</span> nuxt = <span class=\"hljs-keyword\">new</span> Nuxt(config)\n\n<span class=\"hljs-comment\">// Enable live build &amp; reloading on dev</span>\n<span class=\"hljs-keyword\">if</span> (nuxt.options.dev) {\n  <span class=\"hljs-keyword\">new</span> Builder(nuxt).build()\n}\n\n<span class=\"hljs-comment\">// We can use `nuxt.render(req, res)` or `nuxt.renderRoute(route, context)`</span></code></pre><p>You can take a look at the <a href=\"https://github.com/nuxt/express\">nuxt-express</a> and <a href=\"https://github.com/nuxt/adonuxt\">adonuxt</a> starters to get started quickly.</p>\n<h3><a id=\"debug-logs\" class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"#debug-logs\"><svg version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" class=\"octicon octicon-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"/></svg></a>Debug logs</h3><p>If you want to display Nuxt.js logs, you can add the following to the top of your file:</p>\n<pre><code class=\"hljs js\">process.env.DEBUG = <span class=\"hljs-string\">'nuxt:*'</span></code></pre>","docLink":"https://github.com/nuxt/docs/blob/master/en/api/nuxt.md"}]